<TITLE> Quarishi steers middle course in women's policy dispute </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 12 (bdnews24.com)  Progressive Democratic Party convener Ferdous Ahmed Quarishi said Saturday that he had sympathy for those who struggled to establish women's rights, but at the same time, he supported Islamic family law. "The rights Islamic family law allow women to enjoy are scientific, balanced. We support it," Quarishi said at a press conference at the PDP office in Segun Bagicha. He said that his party had support for the people fighting for women's rights too. "There is no scope to disagree on the rights of women. Women were deprived and suppressed for centuries. They have been struggling in patriarchal societies. "But it will be very complex to change the Islamic family law regarding legacy of property," he said. Asked about the release of Sheikh Hasina and Khaleda Zia, the PDP leader said the cases against the two leaders had to be disposed of. "It should be done lawfully. The law cannot bow down to political pressure. The country will be destroyed if the law bends." Asked about the clashes between Islamist hardliners and police, he said: "It's not clear to us how this happened during a state of emergen
